ader":"Two unknowing Hooker lines married in 1825","body":"Laura Woolsey married William Samuel Johnson on April 20, 1825 — a union of two completely independent Hooker descent lines that neither family appears to have recognized. Laura descended through Jonathan Edwards's daughter Mary Edwards Dwight; her husband descended through Jonathan Edwards's son Pierpont Edwards. The Edwards-Hooker stem split four generations earlier and reconverged in their marriage."},{"number":2,"category":"family","header":"Husband's grandfather chaired Constitution drafting committee","body":"Laura's husband William Samuel Johnson (1795-1883) was the grandson and namesake of his celebrated grandfather William Samuel Johnson (1727-1819) — Founding Father, Connecticut delegate to the Constitutional Convention, and chairman of the Committee of Style that drafted the final wording of the U.S. Constitution. The elder Johnson was also U.S. Senator from Connecticut and third president of Columbia University. The 1825 marriage tied the Hooker tree directly to the framing of the Constitution by two routes."}],"slug":"laura-woolsey-1798"},"HD2151":{"id":"HD2151","has_descendants_documented":false,"classification":{"include_in_path_calculation":false,"generation_from_thomas":7,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":true,"descent_from_john_talcott":false,"is_thomas_descendant":true,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_easter_egg":false},"parents":{"father_id":"X00675","mother_id":"HD2095"},"tags":[],"sources":[],"birth":{"year":1797},"gender":"female","marriages":[],"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"death":{},"cross_connections":[],"bio":{"display_name":"Sarah Elizabeth Johnson","first_name":"Sarah","middle_name":"Elizabeth","maiden_name":"Johnson","married_names":[]},"residence":{},"baptism":{},"research_tags":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"artworks":[],"quotes":[],"military_service":[],"slug":"sarah-johnson-1797"},"HD2114"